I'm Mateo. I\'92m 25 years old. I live in Amsterdam, the Netherlands. I\'92m an art student and filmmaker/visual artist \'96 or at least trying to be one. I\'92m writing in English because it\'92s kind of considered a \'91universal' language in our society but there are many other languages too. Many ways to communicate. Many ways to connect to each other, to collaborate, to help, but also to hurt, alienate, dehumanise and deny solidarity to others, whether it is with other humans or with other lifeforms in our ecosystem.\
\
Now it feels like a time where things are falling apart. I always grew up with this idea that we were all, in however minuscule ways, contributing to this huge project of \'91human civilisation\'92. Part of me still believes in that project somehow, that somehow people will remember me, my work and ideas, or maybe just my genes getting passed on.\'a0\
\
But now we don\'92t really know anymore. Our leaders don\'92t have the will to stand up against the profit of a small elite to prevent a catastrophic breakdown of our climate system and the way it facilitates life on our planet. The majority of us are kept ignorant or in denial and we don\'92t seem anywhere close to cause the political revolution that we need in order to actually save our existence as we know it. Paradoxically, the rich people and private companies funding this archive are probably also part of the whole problem in the first place.\
\
Maybe the way some of us deal with the knowledge of our mortality is to convince ourselves of the immortality of a greater kind of self, our human culture.\
